</td></tr></tbody></table></div>
<p><b>Amethyst</b> is a <a href="/Minerals" title="Minerals">Mineral</a> that can be obtained from <a href="/Mining#Mining_Nodes" title="Mining">Amethyst Nodes</a> and <a href="/Mining#Mining_Nodes" title="Mining">Gem Nodes</a> in <a href="/The_Mines" title="The Mines">the Mines</a>, <a href="/Copper_Pan" title="Copper Pan">panning</a>, or as a rare drop from <a href="/Slimes" title="Slimes">Green Slimes</a>. It has a 10% chance to be dropped by a slain <a href="/Dwarvish_Sentry" title="Dwarvish Sentry">Dwarvish Sentry</a> in the <a href="/Volcano_Dungeon" title="Volcano Dungeon">Volcano Dungeon</a>. It may also occasionally be found in <a href="/Fishing#Treasure_Chests" title="Fishing">Fishing Treasure Chests</a> or in a <a href="/Garbage_Can" title="Garbage Can">Garbage Can</a>.  A <a href="/Super_Cucumber" title="Super Cucumber">Super Cucumber</a> <a href="/Fish_Pond" title="Fish Pond">Fish Pond</a> may produce 1-3 Amethyst when the population of the pond reaches 9. The <a href="/Statue_Of_Endless_Fortune" title="Statue Of Endless Fortune">Statue Of Endless Fortune</a> produces one Amethyst per year, on <a href="/Abigail" title="Abigail">Abigail</a>'s birthday, <a href="/Fall" title="Fall">Fall 13</a>.
</p>
